Last week, the Committee of the DG on State Construction and Legislation approved the text of the draft law for second reading, but now it has been revised again.
Now it says that the procedure for taking the oath will be established by the President of the Russian Federation.
Earlier, parliamentarians were going to describe the procedure directly in the law "On Russian citizenship", indicating that the ceremony should be held in a solemn setting in front of the state coat of arms and the flag of Russia in the presence of a representative of the Ministry of Internal Affairs.
