In addition, the text clarifies that restrictions on the occupation of certain positions for foreigners will not apply to those who in writing refused the "other" citizenship and handed over the former passport to the Russian Ministry of Internal Affairs, but "for reasons not dependent on it" it did not cease to be considered a citizen of another country.
Foreigners are now prohibited from occupying positions in the municipal service, to be hired at facilities and in the organization whose activities are related to ensuring the security of Russia.
Also, a person with dual citizenship or residence permit of another country may not become a deputy of the State Duma or a member of the Federation Council.
It is planned that the law should enter into force from 1 September 2017, by that time the necessary sub-legislative acts should be ready.
