The Russian authorities have recently significantly intensified their policy in the Libyan direction, and with visits to Moscow attended delegations of opposing Libyan parties.
The head of the Russian contact group on intra-Libyan settlement at the Russian Foreign Ministry and the State Duma, the assistant to the head of the Chechen Republic, Lev Dengov, told "U", what goals Moscow is pursuing in this region and on whom he is betting.
Almost nothing is known about the contact group on Libya that you head.
Here, let’s say, the contact group on Ukraine – everyone knows about it.
And here's the curtain of mystery.
What exactly do you do, what goals do you pursue?
The contact group was created on the initiative of the Russian Foreign Ministry and the State Duma.
Its activities are supervised by Deputy Foreign Minister Mikhail Bogdanov and Adam Delimkhanov (Deputy of the Duma from Chechnya. - "U").
