We were able to establish contacts with representatives of all the major groups opposing each other in the Libyan conflict - and from Tripoli (where the UN-recognized government headed by Faiz Saraj is based. - "U"), and with Tobruk (the residence of the parliament that opposes the government, the Hafti and supports the marshal.
Thanks to the active participation of Ahmed Metiga (Deputy Prime Minister of Libya - "U"), we were able to quickly agree on the release of Russian sailors.
Then it was decided to make more effective use of these contacts, to create a contact group.
Its task is to analyze the situation, identify key factors and players, dialogue with all sides of the conflict.
In Libya, we do not want to associate with either side of the conflict, we are in dialogue with all.
How many people are in the contact group and how many of them are permanently in Libya?
There are now five people in the contact group.
Among them are people who have experience working in forces, including in the Ministry of Defense.
We also want to include in the team of specialists for the region, representatives of the Institute of the Middle East RAS.
None of our employees are permanently in Libya, and there is no need for this yet.
Whether there are Russian military advisers, instructors in Libya now.
If so, on whose side?
