All conversations and publications about this are not true.
But your contact group's ex-military...
Yes, and their presence is necessary.
For example, when we visit hot spots.
Or cities that were closed to us at some point, such as Misurata (where militia units are based, which played a role in the overthrow of Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi in 2011 and have significantly intensified in the following years.
We arrived in Missouri in January of this year.
We were frightened, we were told that there were Islamists, terrorists.
But it was important for us to assess the situation there ourselves, to analyze the real military potential, who is responsible for what, why such rumors are going on, what is the role of Islamists there.
