And, by the way, we invited people who conducted this anti-terrorist operation to Russia.
And they came - the visit lasted from April 19 to 23 this year, the Libyan delegation was accepted in the Federation Council, in the Duma, the Foreign Ministry and the Rosgvardia.
You, as we understand, are in all regions of Libya and probably imagine the moods of local elites and field commanders.
Do you think it will be possible to implement the agreements on a ceasefire, on the holding of elections, which were reached at the end of July in Paris by Khalifa Haftar and Faiz Saraj?
Or again, as has happened repeatedly in the past, the agreements will be broken, the fighting will resume, the parties will try to seize power alone?
For us, a good signal was already the fact that Saraj and Haftar agreed to another meeting, not so long ago it was impossible.
In the recent past, both leaders have reacted extremely negatively to each other.
Regarding Russia's position...
They often write and say that Moscow actively supports Haftar, many believe it.
We faced this situation when we were in Missouri, and Haftar was on board the Russian aircraft carrier Admiral Kuznetsov on that very day.
It was a coincidence.
But in Missouri, they didn't believe in coincidence.
We were told, “You must be very brave people to come to us today.”
