This herbivorous thyrophore is the best-preserved fossil of its kind in the history of the findings, according to articles in the National Geographic magazine.
He was found by Sean Funk when he was working at the Sankor Millenium mine near Fort McMurray in northern Alberta, Canada, on March 21, 2011.
He stumbled upon something that seemed to be different from the surrounding breed, and decided to take a closer look.
The fossils he discovered were sent to the Royal Tyrrell Museum of Paleontology.
