Researchers believe that this herbivorous thyrophore was hard at work in what is now Canada until a spilling river carried it into the open sea.
But the dinosaur's underwater burial has preserved its shell with precision to the smallest detail.
The fossilized remains of this particular specimen have been so well preserved that the skin remains still cover the bluish armor plates along the dinosaur skull.
