For many decades, the heads of the republic overwhelmed the thresholds of the Moscow cabinets in vain attempts to equalize the region in tariffs with the neighboring Irkutsk region with the cascade of hydroelectric power plants in Angar, which flows from Baikal, the main water catchment area for which is the bury.
And it was only this year that the movements began.
In March, tariffs on electricity for the population of the Republic were reduced from 4.24 rubles/kWh to 3.93 rubles/kWh, or by 7.3%.
With the inclusion of Buryatia by decision of the federal government in the List of territories of price zones of the wholesale market, for which the characteristics of the functioning of wholesale and retail markets are established, industrial consumers have come in.
According to analysts, this is only the beginning, as the population of the Irkutsk region pays per kilowatt hour 1.01 rubles.
But no one dares to name at least an approximate date for the new tariff moves towards a reduction for Buryatia.
