Two months ago, we held a regular meeting in Tolcross with employees and representatives of GMB, at which we openly discussed a number of issues.
We talked to our employees about the fact that, like all companies operating in the most competitive and unstable economic climate, we are constantly reviewing our actions – and this applies to all our facilities and activities – to remain competitive.
“In recent years, we have invested more than <0xC2><0xA3>5 million in our Tolkross facility, especially in production lines and improvements in functional performance.”
We are fully aware of the value of Tolkross as a production facility, and in the event of any changes in the work at this facility, employees and representatives of the trade union will be the first to know about it.”
