In Russia, there will be two new territories of advanced socio-economic development - "Abaza" and "Novotroitsk".
The relevant decrees of the Government of the Russian Federation will enter into force today, August 4.
The boundaries and types of economic activity of TOR on the territory of the city of Abaza in the Republic of Khakassia are defined.
In the city, where 15,000 people live, there will be a special legal regime of business activity, as well as a minimum amount of capital investment of residents, a minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is expected that this will attract about 2.5 billion rubles of investments in the city, and more than 600 new jobs will be created.
In the list of types of economic activities, in which the TOR "Abaza" will operate a special legal regime of business activities, for example, include planting, livestock, production of food, soft drinks and clothing.
The Government of the Republic has already signed framework agreements on the implementation of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependence of the territory on the city-forming enterprise "Abakan Mine" LLC.
In January 2017, the regional authorities reported that Khakassia fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of Economic Development for the creation of the TOR.
The authorities of the Orenburg region did the same.
There, in the city of Novotroitsk, an area of advanced socio-economic development will also be created.
This will allow to diversify the economy of the mono-people, reduce its dependence on the city-forming enterprise of JSC "Uralskaya Stahl", as well as create more than 2,300 jobs and attract investments of more than 8 billion rubles.
The list of economic activities under which a special legal regime for entrepreneurs will operate in the new TOR includes, in particular, freshwater fisheries, the production of feed, medicinal products and medical materials.
Novotroitsk became the first of the monocities of the Orenburg region to receive the status of TOR.
Recall that the territory of advanced development is an economic zone with preferential tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges, which is created to attract investments to improve the lives of the population.
Among the benefits for TOR residents, the following can be distinguished: profit tax of no more than 5% during the first five years, and no less than 10% during the next 5 years, social contributions of 7.6% during 10 years, use of the free customs zone regime, preferential mode of connection to various objects.
